  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    A Business Case takes the Business Opportunity and further develops it in terms of the business solution and includes&#xD;
    costs and benefits. The objective is to understand and document the business opportunity to the point where a go or&#xD;
    no-go decision can be made for implementation project(s). The business requirements and opportunity steps may both be&#xD;
    included in the development of a business case in some organizations. The Business Case facilitates the evaluation,&#xD;
    comparison and prioritization of competing alternatives. The objective is to understand and document the opportunity so&#xD;
    that a decision can be made regarding an implementation&amp;nbsp;project. Which approach is to be taken? What is the scope&#xD;
    of the project?&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_Business_Case&quot; name=&quot;XE_Business_Case&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
